Thanks @r12f . 

@yxieca @wangxin can you help to approve and merge this change? 

This change is used in our 7 node SRv6 test cases only.

@qiluo-msft @ganglyu I addressed one issue with the test due to authentication changes coming from newly added test cases. However, the test still fails. I can see from the logs that the gnmi server on the device receives an Update list instead of a Replace list:

```
I0501 18:52:44.385066 777 server.go:608] Update path: path:{elem:{name:"CONFIG_DB"} elem:{name:"localhost"}}
```

This is the error I would expect if the fix added in https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-buildimage/pull/22355 is not being pulled in. Is there a way to verify whether those changes are being used for these test runs? If so, then there is presumably some issue with the tool fix and I'll need to investigate further. If not, how can we ensure these test runs are using the most up-to-date version of the toolchain?
